Unscheduled power cuts and fluctuating voltage in the rapidly-growing northern suburbs may be a thing of the past with the inauguration of a 66 kV supply line on Saturday.On Saturday, a new sub-station and an upgraded 66 kV line – installed through the novel ‘covered conductor’ technology – was inaugurated by Energy Minister D.K. Shivakumar.The set-up would help KPTCL save nearly Rs. 16 crore in distribution losses. “Many areas around Bengaluru need additional lines. We have drawn up a Rs. 1,400-crore plan to build new lines,” the Minister said.